    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Lightning Spear</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img style="width: 200px; height: 200px;" title="Lightning Spear" src="/file/Elden-Ring/lightning_spear_incantation_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="lightning spear incantation elden ring wiki guide 200px" width="200" height="200"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>Spell Type</td> 
     <td><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dragon Cult Incantations" href="/Dragon+Cult+Incantations" target="">Dragon Cult Incantations</a></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>FP Cost 18</td> 
     <td>Slots Used 1</td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td colspan="2"><img title="item_effect_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_effects_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_55px_18px.png" alt="item effects icon elden ring wiki guide 55px 18px" width="18" height="18">Effect 
      <div class="lineleft">
        Hurls lightning spear before caster 
      </div> <br><img style="float: left;" title="Attributes Requirement" src="/file/Elden-Ring/attributes-required-elden-ring-wiki-guide-18.png" alt="attributes required elden ring wiki guide 18" width="18" height="18">Requires 
      <div class="lineleft"> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Intelligence" href="/Intelligence" target="">Intelligence</a> 0 
       <br> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Faith" href="/Faith" target="">Faith</a> 17 
       <br> 
       <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Arcane" href="/Arcane" target="">Arcane</a>&nbsp;0 
      </div> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Lightning Spear </strong> is an <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Incantations" href="/Incantations" target="">Incantation</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. <strong>Lightning Spear spell</strong> creates a lightning projectile and throws it forward.&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link wiki_tooltip" title="Elden Ring Gravel Stone Seal" href="/Gravel+Stone+Seal">Gravel Stone Seal</a>&nbsp;increases its damage.&nbsp;Updated to&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>One of the incantations of the capital's ancient dragon cult. Summons a lightning spear and hurls it before the caster.<br><br>Charging causes a lightning bolt to strike the point of impact.<br><br>Long ago, Godwyn the Golden defeated the ancient dragon Fortissax, and befriended his fallen foe  an event that gave rise to the ancient dragon cult in the capital.</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Lightning Spear</h3> 
<p>Where to find <strong>Lightning Spear </strong>:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Purchase from <a class="wiki_link wiki_tooltip" title="Elden Ring Brother Corhyn" href="/Brother+Corhyn">Brother Corhyn</a> or&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link wiki_tooltip" title="Elden Ring Miriel Pastor of Vows" href="/Miriel+Pastor+of+Vows">Miriel, Pastor of Vows</a> after giving either the <a class="wiki_link wiki_tooltip" title="Elden Ring Dragon Cult Prayerbook" href="/Dragon+Cult+Prayerbook">Dragon Cult Prayerbook</a>&nbsp;which is dropped by a <a class="wiki_link wiki_tooltip" title="Elden Ring Leyndell Knight" href="/Leyndell+Knight">Leyndell Knight</a> patrolling south of Artist's Shack.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Lightning Spear Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Stamina Cost: 28</li> 
 <li>Deals lightning damage</li> 
 <li>One of the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Dragon Cult Incantations" href="/Dragon+Cult+Incantations">Dragon Cult Incantations</a> and is boosted by the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Gravel Stone Seal" href="/Gravel+Stone+Seal">Gravel Stone Seal</a></li> 
 <li>Enemies seem to ignore this incantation in terms of dodging, meaning under most circumstances Lightning Spear will generally make a successful hit against the enemy. This does not apply to&nbsp;charged version of this incantation.</li> 
 <li>Charging allows you to add small AOE to this single target spell.</li> 
 <li><span style="color: #ff6600;"><em>NOTE:</em></span> Since&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Patch Notes" href="/Patch+Notes">Patch 1.07</a>&nbsp;Attack Power when charged has been Increased&nbsp;</li> 
</ul> 
<div style="max-width: 560px; max-height: 316px;"> 
