				<li id="16524863" class="cmnt-root" data="8" data-d="1647512239000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578210/Lightning-Spear" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">17 Mar 2022 06:17</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16524863" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">After 100+ hours running a Faith/Arcane build, I must say this is the most utilitarian spell of them all. I have had fully charge cast hit above 1k damage and light cast will easily 1 shot trash mobs. Gives splash damage if enemies are close enough. Gets a damage boost in rain/water which is nice considering how often its raining in the overworld. Essentially if you are a Faith build, this is your &quot;R1&quot; move. Mix this with lightning gem buff in Wondrous Physick and is even viable for taking out bosses. I often forget to use other spells, the low FP and stamina cost,  it&apos;s just so viable for everything. <br/>On Torrent this also starts to trivialize the game, I have had the same success with Black Flame. You trot away from the enemy while charging the spell, then when its ready to release, quick turn towards the enemy and release the cast.<br/>A big slow enemy, charge cast. A fast enemy, quick cast. Will catch people off guard in PvP if they get caught, and is a great follow up spell for harder hitting incantations.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16524863" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span cla