				<li id="16506495" class="cmnt-root" data="5" data-d="1647252980000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t578210/Lightning-Spear" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">14 Mar 2022 06:16</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16506495" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">Through testing Ive discovered there are actually 4 stages of the damage this can do depending on exactly how long you charge it. <br/><br/>You can have Fast animation, lowest damage<br/><br/>Fast animation, mid damage<br/><br/>Slow animation, mid damage<br/><br/>Slow animation, high damage<br/><br/>So if you charge it exactly to the point where its behind your head, you get an extra 100 damage or so and get the fast animation. <br/><br/>If you charge it a little slower than that, you get punished with the slow animation without the lightning strike and mid damage.<br/><br/> Holding it down does the highest damage with the slow animation.<br/></p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16506495" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16506495" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">0</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>6</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-do